---
import Heading from "@components/Heading.astro";
import HeadingLarge from "@components/HeadingLarge.astro";
import Text from "@components/Text.astro";
import View from "@components/View.astro";
import Group from "@components/Group.astro";
import { Layout } from "@layouts";
import Image from "@components/Image.astro";
import HeadingSmall from "@components/HeadingSmall.astro";
import TextLink from "@components/TextLink.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Xero | Jonathon Toon | Software Designer, Product Leader"
  description="Jonathon Toon is a versatile software designer and product leader based in Aotearoa New Zealand."
  keywords="design, software, product, fractional, leadership, new zealand, aotearoa, technology, typescript, start ups, engineering, mentorship, coaching, adplist"
  twitterHandle="@jonathontoon"
  canonicalUrl="https://www.jonathontoon.com/"
  ogImage="/images/og-image.png"
>
  <Group>
    <HeadingLarge class="px-2">Xero</HeadingLarge>
    <Text class="px-2">
      Founded in New Zealand in 2006, Xero has grown into one of the world’s
      leading online accounting platforms, helping over 3.5 million small
      business owners and their accountants simplify finances for the better.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      In 2014, I joined a newly formed team in San Francisco as a Mobile Product
      Designer, focused on building Xero’s payroll products across three
      continents.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      As the first hire for the mobile team, I helped shape the team culture and
      influenced the product direction, working closely with the Director of
      Product Design.
    </Text>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <View class="px-2">
      <View class="h-px w-full bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-700" />
    </View>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Heading class="px-2">Xero Me</Heading>
    <Text class="px-2">
      We inherited a product that had seen at least two unsuccessful launch
      attempts. Working with a product manager, engineers, and another designer,
      we had to understand what went wrong.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      Learning from those past efforts, we centered the experience and timed the
      release with XeroCon, Xero's annual conference. We focused only on what
      customers actually needed: easy time-off requests and payslip access.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      I contributed production iOS code, building a polished custom in-app
      notification toast to confirm time-off actions. One of my favorite
      achievements on the project.
    </Text>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Image
      src="/images/work/xero-me-onboarding.png"
      alt="Employee onboarding flow introducing time-off request features."
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    />
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Text class="px-2">
      Despite shipping pressure, I made the time to partner with a researcher to
      run lean testing. I designed the test scenarios and on-device prototypes
      while they handled recruitment.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      A key insight emerged: users wanted the entire date range of time-off
      requests filled in, not just start and end dates. This simple change made
      it immediately clear the full period would be taken.
    </Text>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Image
      src="/images/work/xero-me-request.png"
      alt="Simplified leave request form with calendar integration and visual feedback."
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    />
    <Image
      src="/images/work/xero-me-edit-request.png"
      alt="Request editing with full date range selection based on user research insights."
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    />
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Text class="px-2">
      We shipped mid-2015 across iOS and Android to much fanfare at the
      following year's XeroCon. Business owners and employees had been
      restricted by a dated desktop-only interface, this was their first mobile
      solution for employee management.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      Xero Me is now one of Xero's <TextLink
        target="_blank"
        href="https://www.xero.com/nz/xero-me/">core product offerings</TextLink
      >.
    </Text>
  </Group>
</Layout>
